print(isPalindrome("race a car"))  # Should return False
```

This version of `isPalindrome` continues to ignore spaces, punctuation, and is case-insensitive. The `isAlphanumeric` function checks if a character is alphanumeric, crucial for ignoring spaces and punctuation. The `toLowerCase` function converts a character to lowercase if it's uppercase, ensuring case-insensitivity. The main function, `isPalindrome`, uses these helpers to compare characters from both ends of the string, moving towards the center and skipping any characters that are not alphanumeric.

