To enhance the function to save the state of each ToDo item in local storage and maintain persistence across page reloads, you can follow the steps below. This involves updating the event listener to save the state and modifying the initialization function to load and apply the saved states when the page loads.

```javascript
function addClickListenersToToDoItems() {
  const todoItems = document.querySelectorAll('.todo-item');

  todoItems.forEach(function(item, index) {
    // Set the item's data-index attribute for identification
    item.setAttribute('data-index', index);

    // Load and apply the saved state from local storage
    const itemState = localStorage.getItem('todoItem-' + index);
    if (itemState === 'done') {
      item.classList.add('done');
    }

    // Add click event listener to toggle the done state and save it
    item.addEventListener('click', function() {
      item.classList.toggle('done');
      // Save the state to local storage
      if (item.classList.contains('done')) {
        localStorage.setItem('todoItem-' + index, 'done');
      } else {
        localStorage.removeItem('todoItem-' + index);
      }
    });
  });
}

// Call the function to activate the listeners and load saved states
addClickListenersToToDoItems();
```

This updated function assigns a unique `data-index` attribute to each ToDo item based on its position in the list. This index is used as part of the key in local storage (`todoItem-index`) to save the state of each item. When the page loads, the function checks local storage for each item's state and applies the `done` class accordingly. When an item is clicked, its state is updated in local storage, ensuring that the ToDo list's state persists across page reloads.

Remember, the local storage keys are based on the index of each item in the NodeList returned by `querySelectorAll`, so this approach assumes that the list order does not change. If your application allows reordering of ToDo items, you'll need a more robust way to identify each item, such as a unique ID.

